{"name":"Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Function.ContinuousMapDense","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.Regular","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Function.SimpleFuncDenseLp","Mathlib.Topology.UrysohnsLemma","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.Bochner"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L385-L389","name":"ContinuousMap.toLp_denseRange","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#ContinuousMap.toLp_denseRange","doc":"Continuous functions are dense in `MeasureTheory.Lp`, `1 ≤ p < ∞`. This theorem assumes that\nthe domain is a compact space because otherwise `ContinuousMap.toLp` is undefined. Use\n`BoundedContinuousFunction.toLp_denseRange` if the domain is not a compact space.  "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L368-L374","name":"BoundedContinuousFunction.toLp_denseRange","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#BoundedContinuousFunction.toLp_denseRange","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L331-L352","name":"MeasureTheory.Lp.boundedContinuousFunction_dense","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#MeasureTheory.Lp.boundedContinuousFunction_dense","doc":"A function in `Lp` can be approximated in `Lp` by continuous functions. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L318-L323","name":"MeasureTheory.Integrable.exists_boundedContinuous_integral_sub_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#MeasureTheory.Integrable.exists_boundedContinuous_integral_sub_le","doc":"Any integrable function can be approximated by bounded continuous functions,\nversion in terms of `∫`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L309-L313","name":"MeasureTheory.Integrable.exists_boundedContinuous_lintegral_sub_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#MeasureTheory.Integrable.exists_boundedContinuous_lintegral_sub_le","doc":"Any integrable function can be approximated by bounded continuous functions,\nversion in terms of `∫⁻`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L291-L304","name":"MeasureTheory.Memℒp.exists_boundedContinuous_integral_rpow_sub_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#MeasureTheory.Memℒp.exists_boundedContinuous_integral_rpow_sub_le","doc":"Any function in `ℒp` can be approximated by bounded continuous functions when `0 < p < ∞`,\nversion in terms of `∫`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L239-L286","name":"MeasureTheory.Memℒp.exists_boundedContinuous_snorm_sub_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#MeasureTheory.Memℒp.exists_boundedContinuous_snorm_sub_le","doc":"Any function in `ℒp` can be approximated by bounded continuous functions when `p < ∞`,\nversion in terms of `snorm`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L228-L234","name":"MeasureTheory.Integrable.exists_hasCompactSupport_integral_sub_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#MeasureTheory.Integrable.exists_hasCompactSupport_integral_sub_le","doc":"In a locally compact space, any integrable function can be approximated by compactly supported\ncontinuous functions, version in terms of `∫`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L218-L223","name":"MeasureTheory.Integrable.exists_hasCompactSupport_lintegral_sub_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#MeasureTheory.Integrable.exists_hasCompactSupport_lintegral_sub_le","doc":"In a locally compact space, any integrable function can be approximated by compactly supported\ncontinuous functions, version in terms of `∫⁻`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L197-L213","name":"MeasureTheory.Memℒp.exists_hasCompactSupport_integral_rpow_sub_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#MeasureTheory.Memℒp.exists_hasCompactSupport_integral_rpow_sub_le","doc":"In a locally compact space, any function in `ℒp` can be approximated by compactly supported\ncontinuous functions when `0 < p < ∞`, version in terms of `∫`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L143-L192","name":"MeasureTheory.Memℒp.exists_hasCompactSupport_snorm_sub_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#MeasureTheory.Memℒp.exists_hasCompactSupport_snorm_sub_le","doc":"In a locally compact space, any function in `ℒp` can be approximated by compactly supported\ncontinuous functions when `p < ∞`, version in terms of `snorm`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.lean#L82-L138","name":"MeasureTheory.exists_continuous_snorm_sub_le_of_closed","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/ContinuousMapDense.html#MeasureTheory.exists_continuous_snorm_sub_le_of_closed","doc":"A variant of Urysohn's lemma, `ℒ^p` version, for an outer regular measure `μ`:\nconsider two sets `s ⊆ u` which are respectively closed and open with `μ s < ∞`, and a vector `c`.\nThen one may find a continuous function `f` equal to `c` on `s` and to `0` outside of `u`,\nbounded by `‖c‖` everywhere, and such that the `ℒ^p` norm of `f - s.indicator (fun y ↦ c)` is\narbitrarily small. Additionally, this function `f` belongs to `ℒ^p`. "}]}